This is new updated PR for KAFKA-2000. This is based on discussion from old PR
https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/704.  

@hachikuji @ijuma @harshach

Test doesn't look related. 

@ijuma Is there a particular reason we don't just rely on the nameservice to resolve the address as opposed to validating the config against a regex pattern? If we instead rely on InetAddress.getByName() we can remove any ambiguity which may be caused in the event the regex doesn't match the way we expected it to. This is actually the current behavior as everything before an underscore will be truncated from the hostname leading to some confusion when the following error message includes inaccurate information: 

"DNS resolution failed for url in " + CommonClientConfigs.BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS_CONFIG + ": " + url);

Technically the URL was malformed by the matcher so despite the original URL being resolvable this error will occur. That is quite confusing and we should at an absolute minimum edit the error message.
